[[General (United Kingdom)|General]] '''Sir Bruce Meade Hamilton''' [[Order of the Bath|GCB]], [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] (7 December 1857 &ndash; 6 July 1936) was a [[British Army]] General during [[World War I]].

==Military career==
Hamilton was [[Commissioned officer|commissioned]] into the [[East Yorkshire Regiment]] in 1877.<ref name=lh>[http://www.kcl.ac.uk/lhcma/locreg/HAMILTON6.shtml Liddell Hart Centre for Military Archives]</ref> He served in the [[Second Anglo-Afghan War]] in 1880 and the [[South African War]] in 1881.<ref name=lh/> He became [[Commander]] of the Niger Coast Protectorate Force in [[Benin]] in 1897 and took part in the [[Second Boer War]] in 1900.<ref name=lh/> He played a key role in the capture of ''Naauwpoort''.<ref>[http://samilitaryhistory.org/vol023kg.html South African Military History Society]</ref>

He became [[General Officer Commanding]] [[2nd Infantry Division (United Kingdom)|2nd Division]] within [[Aldershot Command|1st Army Corps]] in 1904 and [[General Officer Commanding]]-in-Chief for [[Scottish Command]] in 1909.<ref name=lh/> He led the Army Command Home Defence during [[World War I]].<ref name=lh/>

